{
  "text": "Interestingly, results obtained with the corresponding SCAND-precipitation correlation monthly patterns present higher correlation values than those obtained with the EA pattern (Fig. 15) . These results are in agreement with those of previous authors that have shown that the SCAND pattern is associated with important precipitation anomalies in both western and eastern Mediterranean regions. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] With the exception of December, all the remaining months are characterized by significant positive correlation values covering the Mediterranean basin. On the contrary, the western half of the Scandinavian peninsula (Norway) presents a persistent, large, negative value, lower then \u22120.6 over some grid boxes. The region between Germany and Poland is also characterized by negative values, particularly between January and March (Fig. 15) .",
